71
00:03:52,825 --> 00:03:58,470
the importance of our team and its specific makeup being key to crafting the franchise

72
00:03:58,510 --> 00:04:02,534
narrative and offering our perspective on characters and story.

73
00:04:02,974 --> 00:04:09,017
We spent ages, just months, figuring it all out, and at every gate reassurances were made

74
00:04:09,057 --> 00:04:12,219
that we're the right people, we'll be able to shape this game, we're going to be fully

75
00:04:12,299 --> 00:04:18,942
embedded and embraced, and we were told specifically that our role as contractors in the studio

76
00:04:18,982 --> 00:04:22,164
would actually give us a lot of freedom and a lot of movement and allow us to do really

77
00:04:22,204 --> 00:04:23,065
specific work.

78
00:04:24,678 --> 00:04:29,643
And so what happened, of course, because this is this talk, is that we joined with a ton of excitement,

79
00:04:30,184 --> 00:04:36,851
but ultimately ended up shoved pretty hard into this internal hierarchy of like this deeply hierarchical place.

80
00:04:37,578 --> 00:04:41,780
Like all of a sudden there were these soft rules about who can speak to who and when.

81
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:47,342
There are these unspoken grudges and politics and some very loudly spoken grudges and politics.

82
00:04:47,742 --> 00:04:52,724
There was public disrespect that we were witnessing happening like in meetings just between developers.

83
00:04:53,345 --> 00:04:57,927
